{"_id":"ElQXAtwrvKjKe7Mb","name":"Mobile Motor Armor","permission":{"default":0,"qtb8j5Fh7Hu0wRrz":3},"type":"npc","data":{"abilities":{"str":{"value":"20","proficient":0,"mod":5,"prof":0,"saveBonus":0,"checkBonus":0,"save":7,"dc":13},"dex":{"value":"10","proficient":0,"mod":0,"prof":0,"saveBonus":0,"checkBonus":0,"save":2,"dc":8},"con":{"value":"10","proficient":0,"mod":0,"prof":0,"saveBonus":0,"checkBonus":0,"save":2,"dc":8},"int":{"value":"10","proficient":0,"mod":0,"prof":0,"saveBonus":0,"checkBonus":0,"save":2,"dc":8},"wis":{"value":"10","proficient":0,"mod":0,"prof":0,"saveBonus":0,"checkBonus":0,"save":2,"dc":8},"cha":{"value":"10","proficient":0,"mod":0,"prof":0,"saveBonus":0,"checkBonus":0,"save":2,"dc":8}},"attributes":{"ac":{"value":"19"},"hp":{"value":35,"min":0,"max":35,"temp":0,"tempmax":0,"formula":""},"init":{"value":0,"bonus":0,"mod":0,"prof":0,"total":0},"spellcasting":"int","speed":{"value":"30 ft","special":""},"prof":2,"spelldc":8},"details":{"biography":{"value":"<p>@Compendium[compendiums-mix-dnd5e.um5-rules.T77zvGdp7mn1uopU]{Exo-Armor Rules &amp; Descriptions} @Compendium[compendiums-mix-dnd5e.um5-rules.1JxfPMXvCWOVqvDw]{Tech Level 4}</p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">This is a generic place-marker for the large variety of custom-designed and prototypical powered armor that appear across the world. These unique designs are simply called mobile motor armors. No two look alike, but they all share similar properties.</span></p>\n<table class=\"NormalTable\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 183px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Mobile Motor Armor </span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 73px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">65,000 </span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 60px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">18* </span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 44px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">&mdash; </span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 81px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Disadvantage </span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 56px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">3,950 lb. </span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 34px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">H </span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 19px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">4</span></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Balance</strong>: For the sake of game balance, the mobile motor armor counts as one legendary item and two very rare items.<br /></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Bonus</strong>: The mobile motor armor has a +1 bonus to AC (19 total).<br /></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Disruption Recovery</strong>: As a reaction to the armor&rsquo;s shutdown, the MMA comes back online. Once you use this feature, you cannot use it again until you finish a long rest.<br /></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Gauntlets</strong>: Unarmed attacks with the armor do base 1d6 damage. If you already inflict 1d6 or more damage with unarmed attacks, increase the damage dice by one step (1d8 &gt; 1d10 &gt; 1d12 &gt; 2d6 &gt; 2d8 &gt; 2d10). The gauntlets also grant a +1 bonus to attack and damage rolls.<br /></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>@Compendium[compendiums-mix-dnd5e.um5-rules.br89VG05tCUMDv4m]{Hit Points &amp; Threshold}</strong>: The mobile motor armor has 35 hit points and a threshold of 5. </span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Large Size</strong>: You are considered a Large creature while wearing the armor. You have reach.<br /></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Mecha Fists</strong>: The mobile motor armor has a Strength of 20.<br /></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Power</strong>: The motor mobile armor requires an H-class power cell to operate and none of its functions work<br />without it. @Compendium[compendiums-mix-dnd5e.um5-equipment.JKcEAJ4xm2Us5hYN]{Battry Cell, High}<br /></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Speed</strong>: Your speed is 30 feet.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Resistances</strong>: You gain resistance fire, acid, and cold, as well as bludgeoning, and slashing from nonmagical weapons.<br /></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Removable Weapon Limbs</strong>: You can remove a gauntlet and replace it with a heavy weapon mount. Because the mobile motor armor is Large, you can install super heavy weapons as heavy weapons. Likewise, you can install heavy weapons or two-handed small arms in these mounts as two-handed small arms and one-handed small arms, respectively.</span></p>","public":""},"alignment":"","race":"","type":"","environment":"","cr":1,"spellLevel":0,"xp":{"value":200},"source":""},"traits":{"size":"lg","di":{"value":[],"custom":""},"dr":{"value":["acid","bludgeoning","cold","fire","slashing"],"custom":""},"dv":{"value":[],"custom":""},"ci":{"value":[],"custom":""},"senses":"","languages":{"value":[],"custom":""}},"currency":{"pp":0,"gp":0,"ep":0,"sp":0,"cp":0},"skills":{"acr":{"value":0,"ability":"dex","bonus":0,"mod":0,"prof":0,"total":0,"passive":10},"ani":{"value":0,"ability":"wis","bonus":0,"mod":0,"prof":0,"total":0,"passive":10},"arc":{"value":0,"ability":"int","bonus":0,"mod":0,"prof":0,"total":0,"passive":10},"ath":{"value":0,"ability":"str","bonus":0,"mod":5,"prof":0,"total":5,"passive":15},"dec":{"value":0,"ability":"cha","bonus":0,"mod":0,"prof":0,"total":0,"passive":10},"his":{"value":0,"ability":"int","bonus":0,"mod":0,"prof":0,"total":0,"passive":10},"ins":{"value":0,"ability":"wis","bonus":0,"mod":0,"prof":0,"total":0,"passive":10},"itm":{"value":0,"ability":"cha","bonus":0,"mod":0,"prof":0,"total":0,"passive":10},"inv":{"value":0,"ability":"int","bonus":0,"mod":0,"prof":0,"total":0,"passive":10},"med":{"value":0,"ability":"wis","bonus":0,"mod":0,"prof":0,"total":0,"passive":10},"nat":{"value":0,"ability":"int","bonus":0,"mod":0,"prof":0,"total":0,"passive":10},"prc":{"value":0,"ability":"wis","bonus":0,"mod":0,"prof":0,"total":0,"passive":10},"prf":{"value":0,"ability":"cha","bonus":0,"mod":0,"prof":0,"total":0,"passive":10},"per":{"value":0,