{"_id":"GVlEewjAiVTGDu1O","name":"Combat Exoskeleton (TL5)","permission":{"default":0,"qtb8j5Fh7Hu0wRrz":3},"type":"npc","data":{"abilities":{"str":{"value":"23","proficient":0,"mod":6,"prof":0,"saveBonus":0,"checkBonus":0,"save":8,"dc":14},"dex":{"value":"10","proficient":0,"mod":0,"prof":0,"saveBonus":0,"checkBonus":0,"save":2,"dc":8},"con":{"value":"10","proficient":0,"mod":0,"prof":0,"saveBonus":0,"checkBonus":0,"save":2,"dc":8},"int":{"value":"10","proficient":0,"mod":0,"prof":0,"saveBonus":0,"checkBonus":0,"save":2,"dc":8},"wis":{"value":"10","proficient":0,"mod":0,"prof":0,"saveBonus":0,"checkBonus":0,"save":2,"dc":8},"cha":{"value":"10","proficient":0,"mod":0,"prof":0,"saveBonus":0,"checkBonus":0,"save":2,"dc":8}},"attributes":{"ac":{"value":"17"},"hp":{"value":45,"min":0,"max":45,"temp":0,"tempmax":0,"formula":""},"init":{"value":0,"bonus":0,"mod":0,"prof":0,"total":0},"spellcasting":"int","speed":{"value":"30 ft","special":""},"prof":2,"spelldc":8},"details":{"biography":{"value":"<p>@Compendium[compendiums-mix-dnd5e.um5-rules.T77zvGdp7mn1uopU]{Exo-Armor Rules &amp; Descriptions} @Compendium[compendiums-mix-dnd5e.um5-rules.aMZgpx4YpHpEBjf8]{Tech Level 5}</p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The combat exoskeleton resembles an oversized piece of medieval plate, reinforced by limbs of titanium and amplified by synthetic muscle fibers running through the entire assembly. Though not very pretty, the ComExo has proved its usefulness in combat.</span></p>\n<table class=\"NormalTable\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 92px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Combat Exoskeleton </span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 67px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">85,000 </span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 185px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">15*+Dex modifier (max 2) </span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 39px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">&mdash; </span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 81px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Disadvantage </span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 44px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">1,950 lb. </span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 12px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">H </span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 24px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">5</span></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><strong>Balance</strong>: <span class=\"fontstyle0\">The TL5 combat exoskeleton counts as two legendary items and one very rare item.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Bonus</strong>: The TL5 combat exoskeleton has a +2 bonus to AC (17 total).<br /></span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Disruption Recovery</strong>: As a reaction to the armor&rsquo;s shutdown, the combat exoskeleton comes back online. Once you use </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"font-size: 11pt;\">disruption recovery</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">, you cannot use it again until you finish a long rest. </span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Gauntlets</strong>: Unarmed attacks with the armor do base 1d6 damage. If you already inflict 1d6 or more damage with unarmed attacks, increase the damage dice by one step (1d8 &gt; 1d10 &gt; 1d12 &gt; 2d6 &gt; 2d8 &gt; 2d10). The gauntlets also grant a +1 bonus to attack and damage rolls.<br /></span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>@Compendium[compendiums-mix-dnd5e.um5-rules.br89VG05tCUMDv4m]{Hit Points &amp; Threshold}</strong>: The TL5 combat exoskeleton has 45 hit points and a threshold of 5. </span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Mecha Fists</strong>: The TL5 combat exoskeleton has a Strength of 25.<br /></span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Power</strong>: The combat exoskeleton requires an H-class power cell to operate and it does not function without it. @Compendium[compendiums-mix-dnd5e.um5-equipment.JKcEAJ4xm2Us5hYN]{Battry Cell, High}<br /></span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0